時折思い出しては見に来たくなります。
2020東京オリンピックは、日本では裏金問題や数々の炎上問題などがあり、必ずしも順風満帆な大会ではありませんでした。
ですが、開催に際して公開されたこちらの映像作品にはじまり、一生懸命精進する選手さんの方々にはとてもワクワクさせていただきました。
こちらの東京をモチーフとした爽快な歌謡、映像をはじめてみた時の感動は、今なお色褪せることがありません。

text: Umm... I'm a Japanese, and really embarrassed to imagine a strange view for Tokyo from overseas. First, the scene of a street full of shops beside and crowded people reminds me of a street in OSAKA, not in TOKYO. Second, recently, there have not been the game-playing people in a small shop inside; the corona pandemic has already driven away those people, and such game shops run by companies, like SEGA, have been closed Third, in the latter half of this movie, there is a city view of many blue lights in night. Of course, even at midnight, some districts, like Shimjuku, are light and crowded. But, to tell the truth, there is not anywhere full of only one color.

text: 🌏自然とともにひとり一人の命をつなぐ本当の意味での東日本大震災を真剣に考えないと明日の日本は無い。復興五輪をやっている暇は無い。福島原発事故は今も解決していない。原発維持を言っていた安倍前首相の時に真剣に反原発を考えて行ったら生活不安や健康被害を考えるチャンスに成った。安倍前首相の判断の積み重ねからミスや過ちを犯し、外国で起きた原発事故を考えていれば廃炉や新エネルギーがもっと前に進んでいた。今も尚、生活不安や健康被害をもたらす日本の原発は原発が出来た時に問題課題が有っただから教訓から学ばない原発維持の安倍前首相の判断の積み重ねからミスや過ちをもたらした。🌏自然と向き合いひとり一人の命を守りひとり一人と寄り添って生きる力が反原発や廃炉や新エネルギーを考える日本人です。🌎🌍🌏脱原発とともにほんものの自然の力が心を強くする生きる力🌏🌍🌎過去を顧みてこそ未来がある日本社会🗾🌏ほんものの自然を残す事が嘘偽りのない自然の力が生きる力です。🌏ほんものとは、自然を壊さず地球を汚さないでつくったもの。自分の良心に訴えて恥ずかしくないもの。人をだまさんもののことである。自然は私達ひとり一人を見ています。私達ひとり一人の生命も自然です。🌏
author: @自然の力と共にいまを生きる嘘

text: 🌍国会を蔑ろに国会答弁も出来ない政治介入の自民党菅政治を問い正す事が命と暮らしを守るほんものの政治です。🌍パンデミックの負の五輪の政治利用する東京オリンピックを問い直す事が命と暮らしを守る日本人です🌍政治利用や平和利用する政治家はスポーツを語る資格なし🌍政治利用しない事がほんもののスポーツです。🌍パンデミックの世界中に混乱を招く東京オリンピックを問い直す事がほんもののオリンピック精神です🌍
author: @自然の力と共にいまを生きる嘘

text: 🌏生まれ変わる世界とともにひとり一人の生命を守る事が求められる国際社会🌎手を差し伸べる現場ひとり一人の声を聞く耳を澄ませることが思いやる想像力と知恵を使って、支え合う豊かなコミュニティを国のすみずみに作っていくゆくことが、ひとり一人に寄り添っていく命と暮らしを守るこれからの社会だと思います。そんな大人たちの姿はきっと、子供たちの胸に未来への希望を灯すでしょう。🌏大変なコロナ禍だからこそわれわれ市民が常に心にとどめておかないといけないのは、決して忘れないということ。そして黙らないということだ。それ以外に社会人としての使命は果たせない。🌏生まれ変わる世界とともに忘れない黙らない現場ひとり一人の発信力と共に誰もが誰かに助けられて生きていていることに気づかせる共同体の存在を現場ひとり一人の精神を世界中に広げてゆく。どうか皆さん現場ひとり一人の歓声とともに一緒に頑張りましょう🌍大変なコロナ禍だからこそ現場ひとり一人の声を知る力が求められる国際社会🌏

text:
The Olympics must not exhibit any political or biased tendencies.  The host country, Japan, is also disseminating this information to athletes and officials who participated in the Olympics.  
But Japan, meanwhile, asked the IOC to require that athletes who participated in the Olympics pay a silent tribute to the victims on the day the atomic bomb was dropped on Hiroshima.  
The dropping of the atomic bomb on Hiroshima was not an easy decision made by the United States, the Allied Powers at the time, in that Japan, a war criminal country, did not give up on the war and continued to kill innocent people.  
Remembrance of the victims of the atomic bombing is no different from forcing people to visit Japanese shrines.  
This double aspect of Japan does not qualify as a host country for the Olympics, a place of global harmony, and even after the IOC rejected Japan's request to commemorate the atomic bombing, the Tokyo 2020 Olympic Committee said they plans to include a performance that  commemorate the victims of the atomic bombing in this Olympic closing ceremony. This proves that Japan has not yet abandoned its role as a war criminal country rather than an Olympic host country.  
I hope that the people of the world will face this double aspect of Japan and correct their misconceptions about Japan. I also demand the IOC not to tolerate this double act of Japan, the host country of the Olympics, and take corresponding measures.

text:
무한극락은 발전이 끝이 있고--고통의 종말-- 무한극락발전은 끝이 없다--

무상정등각--
변화 인연 생성 모순 긍정무한 무한와중 무한와중발전 무한극락 무한극락발전--

마음은 무한자기다--

무한은 모든 것들을 품어준다--무한은 현재와 순간에서 모든 것이(비논리 역설 모순 횡설수설 등이) 가능하다--

연결주의-연기론이 존재론을 품어준다--연결와중-연결와중발전--연결극락--연결극락발전--

니체의 영혼--현실에 안주하지 말고 위험하게도 살 수 있어야 된다--

이승세계와 사바세계는 분별이 없다--자타일여--
사바세계가 무한이다--

연결주의-인연연결이 존재론과 정신분석과 현대철학 모두를 품는다--
억지생각은 방하해야 된다--

중도 연결 융합--

상호의존해서 화합한다--

무한극락--영원한 자유--

무한과 부처님--무한이 부처다--
무한은 모든 종교를 품어준다--
불교의 자비는 상호의존 융합 화합이고, 자비는 모든 것을 가능케 해준다--

무한은 엄마다--

불생불멸이 끝이 없는 무한이다--

무한은 자비다--
무한은 모든 장애를 해결해준다--
불교의 자비는 무한이라는 다른 이름이다--
무한이 현전과 순간을 품어준다--
모든 근거가 무한이다--

무한이 모든 유한을 품어준다--

생멸인연이 무한에서 온다--
무한이 모든 유한을 가능케 한다--
무한으로 말미암아 모든 것을 성립시킨다--
무한이 유한을 품는다--

무한이 모든 것을 품는다--
무한-자비가 공과 무상 무아 연기 중도를 품는다--
모든 것이 무한에서 온다--

text:
Japan to allow the Rising Sun flag in the Olympics

 The Rising Sun Flag is a flag that symbolizes the sun spreading in 16 branches around the sun in an existing red circle.  The Japanese government is in a position to allow the Rising Sun flag at the 2020 Tokyo Olympics.  They maintain the attitude that "they have no political intent and are merely a flag widely used in Japan."

 The Rising Sun Flag, which was the flag of the former Japanese Empire in the 19th century, is remembered as a “symbol of Japanese militarism” in Korea and China, which were victims of Japanese military aggression in the 20th century.  The Japanese government is using the flag symbolizing war crimes even though it has not paid due compensation to the victims and has not fully reflected on its own history.  In fact, the Rising Sun Flag is the flag of the Japan Maritime Self-Defense Force, and is the flag used by far-right forces in Japan.

 For this reason, the South Korean government has criticized the “Rising Sun Flag as a flag of hatred.” An associate professor of history at the University of Hawaii, analyzed Japan's behavior, saying, "The current Japanese government has been neglecting the rise of extreme nationalist forces and has been using nationalist expressions politically."

text:
在美帝的控制下，国家没有正常化的日本最终其历史文化还是被阉割了。因为只有国家正常化了，其本土民族真正站起来了，才能有政治条件来正视那段侵略的历史，这个民族长远才会有希望。
客观的讲，这个视频的观赏性还是可圈可点的。但是这个8分钟里只讲了科技而没有文化，缺少了日本本国的历史底蕴，和我国国师在平昌的8分钟立意上还是差了很多。
关于日本的侵略史，这个作为国人都会对其感到厌恶。其实日本本土的知识分子也是这样的，当年赤军也不是开玩笑的。只可惜因为美国的控制终究还是只能当美国的狗。关于历史道歉问题，其实日本高层人士对于侵华战争对中国道歉的人士在维基上甚至还专门列了一个清单。只可惜亲华派都被美帝碾死了（如安倍晋三第一任，松下忠洋等等）。因此请大家擦亮眼睛，美帝才是我们真正的对手！东亚搞(RCEP)于是韩中萨德，日中钓鱼岛，日韩竹岛（中日韩自贸区），南海危机（东盟以及海上一带一路），哈萨克斯坦变种疫情（陆上一带一路）等等.
只有日韩两国真正国家正常化了，那么东亚自贸区才能搞成。三个同文同种的民族才能得到真正的发展！

text:
パリ五輪関連記事で「東京五輪のピクトグラムは誰も傷つけない素晴らしいパフォーマンスだった」的なことを言われていて久しぶりに見たくなった。

やっぱり、見れば見るほど小林賢太郎のパフォーマンスのセンスだし、これが東京五輪の開会式の中でも高い評価を得てるのが彼のファンとしては嬉しい。
特に、 2:31 からの手を使ったパフォーマンスは本当に小林賢太郎のパフォーマンスで見たかったと感じてしまう。

その一方で、「誰も傷つけない」って言われるようなパフォーマンスを作った人が、過去のネタの件で降ろされたのが残念でならない。名前は出さないのに、演出プランだけ盗むんだ、へぇ。という気持ちになる。

text:
ものすごく小林賢太郎さんみを感じる。わかる人にはわかるだろう。
人を傷つけない笑いを作るに至った方の「今」を評価しないで、「過去」の若さをほじくり返して足を引っ張る。
こういうアイデアだけ盗んで、今頃になってピクトグラムのとこは良かった、とか言う。
彼をはじめ、素晴らしい才能あるクリエーターをことごとく嫌な目に遭わせたのが悲しい。
それでも今、改めてこのピクトグラムの演出が賞賛されるなら、慰めになるのかな。
私はずっと彼の作品のファンです。

text:
パリ五輪が物議をかもした関係でこの動画を見つけました。
視聴が初めての人間にも、「64年から二度目の東京開催」「歴代五輪開催国の中での日本らしさ」が一目で理解できる素晴らしいオープニングパフォーマンスだと思います。

それとセーリング(3:25)やボート(4:06)など、華麗さだけでないコメディーチックな面白さも織り込まれているのが笑いを誘って楽しいです。

text:
自分語り失礼します。
2021年、ちょうど小6でした
運動会のときドラクエで入場して、自分たちで創作したピクトグラムやったんです
グループごとにやってたんですが私たちは自撮りとかジョジョ立ちとかそんなことしてました(笑)
コロナが蔓延してみんなで何ができるだろうかなんて考えてた時、スポーツにも何にも興味がなかったあの時の私も東京五輪のオープニングとこのピクトグラムだけは食い入るように見ていたのを覚えています
今でもこうやって見に来てしまいます
大好きです

text:
仏・巴里五輪開会式からこの動画を見に来た方が多いこと。w
東京五輪の開会式で全50競技を3人のパントマイマーがピクトグラム(ピクトグラフ)を演じて、だれもが傷つかないのを証明している。
巴里五輪が想像以上にやらかして、五輪公式(CIO または IOC)が巴里五輪開会式動画を削除したのは、一応「これはやばい」という認識をしているんでしょう。今更遅いのですが、欧米人からすればババに砂かけて無かったことにするのを体現したと思いますがね。w
author: @早地峯カクラ

text: 削除すればいいってものじゃない。確かに「見どころ」はあったパリ五輪の開会式は半永久的に人々の記憶に残る羽目になりました
author: @macha3009

text:
あの世界中から批判を浴びたパリ五輪の開会式を見てからだと、東京五輪のこのピクトグラムを用いたパフォーマンスって素晴らしいなと思ってしまう。
ピクトグラムは誰かが信仰する宗教を傷つけないし、黒人・白人・黄色人種の区別もないし、性別も感じさせず、誰が見ても一目で何を表しているのか分かる。
平和で平等な誰もが使える可愛い図記号。

text:
この芸風は完全にコバケンなので、好きな人はラーメンズの名作を漁るといいかもしれません。
小林賢太郎（コバケン）というのは難癖でキャンセルされた人ですが、彼は舞台公演で役者と脚本を兼ねており、「生で人が動く舞台ならではのワチャワチャ感」を笑いや感動に繋げる術に長けていました。彼の特技はパントマイムであり、途中に挟まる映像の一部が『日本の形』にそっくりなことからも、案のほとんどは恐らく彼が降ろされる前に残していたものでしょう。
彼の名前が残らないのは極めて残念な事ですが、せめて彼の作品が評価されているのは救いかもしれません。
しかし、ああ、最後までコバケンが監修した開会式を私は見たかった。
author: @lv1754

text:
私も、ラーメンズの演劇的かつコミカルなコントが大好きで、過去作（しかも揶揄）をやり玉に小林さんが降ろされてしまった件はずっとモヤモヤしていました（しかも今回のパリの差別的とも取れる演出が世界に披露できたのに）
あなたのコメントに出会えて、当時からこのピクトがなんだかうるっとくるくらい大好きだった理由がわかった気がします
ありがとうございます
author: @ゆうべ

text: @@ゆうべ 委員会の立場のためか名言はされてないですけど、このピクトグラムの出し物はコバケンが素案をほぼ全部作ったのはまず間違いないですからね。その感覚を言葉に出来たのなら何よりです。

text: Esto fue Patético y no tiene justificación, el juego no se acaba hasta que se acaba, 2 horas de competición y ya se rinden en buscar un ganador🤦🏻‍♂️ John Isner y Nicolás Mahut compitieron por 11 horas en Wimbledon 2010 y no era ni siquiera la final! Eso es ser competitivo, verdadero espíritu deportivo y ser respetuoso con la disciplina. Grandioso hubiera sido que compitieran hasta desfallecer y encontrar un ganador después de una dura competición, pues se trataba de la final. John Isner ganó el partido, pero perdió la siguiente ronda por su agotamiento, mientras que estos tipos no tenían que competir más después de esto. Vergonzoso lo que ocurrió aquí, si se tratara de amistad, lo mejor seria que desde el comienzo no hubieran competido y medallas de oro para todos, nadie obtiene plata y bronce. Todos ganan oro solo por participar y que viva la amistad🤦🏻‍♂️ lo más triste es que disfracen la mediocridad con el valor de la amistad y mucha gente crea que esto es algo bueno, cuando es algo que le falta el respeto al deporte. Pues la amistad es importante, pero lo primordial es la competencia.

text: The shared gold was a moment of pure track and field gold (pun intended) but this Olympic final was by far the best performing for the largest amount of athletes. To get a medal you would have to jump less than an inch (2 cm) below the Olympic RECORD. 10 people were still jumping at the height of 2.35 m or 7’8. This is insane when you think that just making it to that height would give you a medal in every other Olympic final in but 2. Let alone clearing that height gets a medal in all but 1 Olympic Final. Historic.

text: I can't believe how many crazy (probably american) users have commented about him being "black" and "not italian". Maybe it's time to be humble and learn something about the rest of the world. In America "italians" are people who are not italian at all, but "italian-americans" i.e. descendants of immigrants coming especially from small villages of southern Italy. In this sense an Italian (meaning italian american) cannot be black. And that's why you get confused. In Italy an Italian is just a person who has italian citizenship, who was brought up in Italy, speaks italian, identifies with our nation and with our culture. So you can be Italian AND black, just like you can be French and black, for instance. Jacobs is Italian, we can say that he is half american because his father is american but we italians don't give a f** about identifying him as black or putting him in a box for "ethnicity", "race", "colour of the skin", "appearance" and all this nonsense and paranoia you have overseas about it. He's Italian. Period. Besides that, he has always trained in Italy so I guess Italian coaches are phenomenal if they did this with him, while in America they have lots of african american athletes and you were not able to win this medal or the 4x100. Sorry.

text: 9 seasons, 2008 - 2016 Usain Bolt was untouchable. 3 Olympic Games and 4 world championships in athletics. 6 gold medals in 100 m, 7 gold medals in 200 m, 7 gold medals in 4 x 100 m - a total of 20 gold medals, the owner of the current incredible world records in 100 m, 200 m and 4 x 100 m, he broke other people's and his own records 7 times. I absolutely do not believe that anyone will come along who will achieve such continuity even close to Bolt. I don't know how it is for others, but for me, after Bolt, the sprint disciplines are now quite average, that is, what they were before him, with the difference that they were the top then, and now they are average - Bolt's shadow will forever cover the sprint disciplines.

text:
Thank you for reminding me about this one of the greatest memories of Olympic ever. 

So sad the opening ceremony in 2020(+1) was destroyed by corruptions. 
I still hope that I can see a show by the original team ,MIKKO & Sheena Ringo, someday. 

Also… I felt something was wrong in 2020 game but now I guess Olympic had been slowly slowly corrupted every time. I just couldn’t realize that till 2020 started but that was too late. 

Sadly, I don’t feel the same value for Olympics as before because of many things relating to Olympic these days… 
It may had have some shady stuff all the time, because it’s a huge event with tons of money, but I remember people used to simply enjoyed sports more before(could be I was just too young to realize the real).

Wasn’t that the Olympic the festival of sports and peace ,without any politics and discrimination but with respect and sportsmanship…? 

Now it seems all about money and ideology….

007, 몬티 파이튼, 미스터빈, 퀸, 비틀즈 등이 출연한 그들의 공연은 영국이 현대에 일궈낸 문화적 성과를 여과없이 보여주는 특별한 모습이었다.

그리고 4년이 지난 2016년 리우데자네이루, 브라질의 폐막식보다도 더 많은 기대를 가지게 했던게 2분짜리 도쿄의 퍼포먼스가 아니었나 싶다.

author: @sherryleona9079

text: It was all Dentsu’s fault, they ousted Mikiko, who did this handover ceremony. Her original plans for the Tokyo Olympic ceremonies was suppose to include Super Mario, Jpop, and Akira Motorcycle. She was disgustingly sidelined by Hiroshi Sasaki. I’m spreading awareness about this so that people will know who is at fault here and Japanese people are blaming Dentsu, Hiroshi Sasaki, and Yoshiro Mori for the way how Tokyo Olympic ceremonies turned out.
author: @crozzxj8556

text: If you want to know who is to blame for how the Tokyo Olympic ceremonies turned out, it’s all Yoshiro Mori, Mr Hiroshi Sasaki, and Dentsu’s fault. Mikiko was the original director who directed this performance and she originally was suppose to direct the 2020-21 Olympics ceremonies but she quit because of how she was treated dirty by Sasaki, Mori, and Dentsu. People like Mikiko try to make Japan look great on stage yet there’s the old farts like Yoshiro Mori and Hiroshi Sasaki who successfully made Japan look bad by being greedy . Also Dentsu got greedy for money, which is why the actual ceremonies was poorly done by them. The new poorly done ceremony was directed by Sasaki, who later then resigned after making fun of Naomi Watanabe’s weight, after he successfully forced Mikiko out. Also, Kentaro Kobayashi was appointed by Sasaki himself to direct the ceremonies after he resigned, and he himself was ousted the day before the opening ceremony of the Tokyo Olympics. So therefore, Covid was not to entirely blame, it was the fault of incompetent people like Mr Sasaki, Mr Mori, and the advertising company Dentsu who ruined the original Tokyo Olympic opening ceremonies plans with Akira, Super Mario etc directed by Mikiko and it all got replaced by trash performances made by problematic people like Sasaki

text:
RIP Mr Abe.

Another note: for those of you who don't know, the blue character providing the tunnel for Mario at 1:29 is called Doraemon. He is a humanoid cat-type robot from 2112AD. He provides unimaginable gadgets from the future using his "4th dimensional pouch". While his peers have ears similar to cats, his got bitten off by a rat so he has developed severe phobia towards rats. 

This character was drawn up in the early 1980s. His gadgets were highly futuristic and unimaginable by 1980s standards. But with the advent of computers, AI and the internet, a lot of them have already been materialized nowadays.

text:
I believe what we now experienced,  is a modest athlete first oriented Japanese olympic games that should deserve the actual sequel if the dark days of the pandemic are over one day.

I believe Japan deserves a real grand post pandemic Olympics in tokyo. In memorial and reward of it's modesty carefulness and resilience for both Sporters and it's people during the hardest times of today.

So it should be still called tokyo 2020 , and That event should become the highlight of Japanese culture in the 21st century. We would probably have seen Mario popping out into the stadium after a long time gone fighting the virus for years as a doctor,  Dr. Mario 🤣

 Why should we follow the 4 years rule when this is possible? As for if you wondering Japan is broke after this pandemic phase , Japan has already secured the Asian games the next decade , and announced bidding for a winter games in Sapporo in the future as well. I don't see Japan being tired . 

But I believe we should go for real Olympics games with the real fans for Japan in our times after the pandemic. 

The directors who made this movie above,  deserves another chance because the pandemic isn't their fault. 
But this time with the ideas that has been kept away. 

Spoilers:

At the closing ceremony , the flame has basically been softly curbed into a frozen ball .

🌸 I have the ambition to continue the dream for tokyo 2020 summer Olympics in memorum. 🌸

Any Japanese people  who have here have a take?

2012년 런던올림픽 당시, 영국이 자국의 문화를 거리낌없이 보여주면서 문화강국이란 것이 무엇이였는지 보여준것처럼 일본역시 그동안 쌓아온 자국의 문화를 아낌없이 보여줄수 있었을텐데 정말 아쉽고 안타깝다.
정말보고싶었던 것은 아키라의 카네다 바이크가 도쿄올림픽 개막을 알리는 것을 보고싶었는데 말이다

text:
毎回、元々、五輪開会式は、会場内の人達以外の
世界中の殆どの人達は「映像で」観ることになっていた。
まして今回は結果的に「無観客で」、いつもに増して殆どの人は、
「映像で」観ることになった。
それならば、当初のMIKIKO案を実施し、映像で流すだけで良かった。

コロナ禍でも、リモートワークの様に、開会式を映像で、
毎回と同様に楽しんでもらうことができたはず。

あくまでも乗っ取りは、反日の電通などの思惑であり、
コロナ禍を上手く利用されただけ。

繰り返すが、コロナ禍でも、「映像」でMIKIKO案を世界中の
方達を楽しますことができた。

「コロナのせいで」「コロナ禍だからしょうがない」というのは
電通の悪行を逃そうとする世論誘導に過ぎません。

text:
この映像を見る度にも悲しくなります
日本の各種アニメーション（ドラえもん、ドラゴンボール、ポケモン、任天堂キャラクター、ジブリ）のような日本の有名キャラクターが出演する予定であり、この広報映像よりも素敵なオリンピックになる予定だったが、中国のコロナにより90％以上のスポンサーが撤退とは全く関係中の予算が不足して質素にオリンピックの戦いされた日本の姿が韓国人である私が見てもとても残念とかわいそうでした。このような事実を知らずにむやみにみすぼらしいオリンピックとする愚かな人々のために腹が立ちます、元の予定された華やかな開幕式と閉幕式、満杯になった観客席の中の歓声などがすべて削除されたことを考慮すると、2020東京オリンピックは歴代最高のオリンピックになる予定であり、このような切ない状況を考慮した私の心の中では最も記憶に残る歴代最高のオリンピックです負けない日本の
また、感謝してい、日本
世界のために犠牲にした日本に感謝して

text:
演出担当の旧チームは予算削減を打診されたとき「それならば、入場行進だけにしましょう」と提案したという噂もありました。
時は過ぎて今日、日本の高校野球大会の開会式では
ドラマでの配役に関連して、ミュージカル俳優の山崎育三郎さんが白いブラウスに黒いパンツというシンプルな装いで歌を一曲歌い上げました。
ただ立って歌うだけ、というとてもシンプルなものなのに
それはそれは、心に響く歌声で、「あぁ、予算を削減したところで人の心を感動させることはできるじゃないか。きっと旧チームの皆さんなら入場行進だけでもワクワクさせてくれたんだろう。」と妙に納得してしまいました。

text:
一晩経っても昨日の閉会式(開会式含め)の質の酷さに憤りを感じる。
MIKIKOさんの開会式案、マリオやドラえもんの他にも、孫悟空やピカチュウも出演する予定だったんですよね。
他にも様々な魅力的な演出。
残念でしかない。
CGでもいいから、お金も払うから、再現してほしい。
そして、それをもってMIKIKOさんのハイセンスと、電通のナンセンスを世界に発信してほしい。

〈追記〉
MIKIKOさんが辞任された経緯について週刊文春が記事にしていましたが、それが本当なら、もうお願いだから、森や小池みたいなド素人をクリエイティブに関わらせないでほしい。
また今回の一連の顛末を不満に思う電通のインハウスデザイナーもいらっしゃるんでしょうが、電通が組織としてクリエイティブを蔑ろにするような対応しかできないなら、電通も今後クリエイティブには関わらないでほしい。

text:
Is this real Japan? Oh My God… What have you done this opening/closing ceremony? Japan has so many spectacular culture contents. I had looked for to opening/closing ceremony since Rio closing ceremony. Your cultural contents are superb among the whole world, including Kareoke, Joe Hisaishi, Ghibli, Nintendo, Emoji, Jpop or Jrock, Anime or Game OST, QR Code, Ninja, Samurai, Sakura, Acoustic Cafe, Ryuichi Sakamoto, Yuhki Kuramoto, Hatsune Miku, Anime(pikachu, doraemon, and etc..), Godzilla, Gundam, Game, and so many things. I think if this contents had been presented, it would have been the Greatest and Finest of all time legend opening/closing ceremony, even exceeding London 2012. 

BUT!!! 
What the heck is this opening/closing ceremony??? what is the story of the whole performances? I didn’t understand what you showed me. It is just basic and rustic, and is not interesting to look and feel. The Tokyo Olympic officials have to reconsider your performance. It was really disappointing.

text:
このクオリティだったから、5年もの間東京オリンピックを待ち遠しくてたまらないぐらい期待してたのに…個人的に想像以上の完成度だと思ったら想像以下でした。そのおかげで5年間水の泡になるぐらい、あっけなく終わってしまった感じで、この先二度とないかもしれない東京オリンピックを台無しにしたと言っても過言じゃないと思う。
ともかく地味で「意味不明」。紅蓮華流れたときは鬼滅好きだけど、何でもかんでも鬼滅って感じでセンスがなかったし、鬼滅以外にも他のアニメも登場してほしかった。
なにより安倍マリオが登場しなかったのガチでショック。

text:
はぁ…悲しいし本当に悔しいです。
開会式に限らず閉会式までも情け無い終わり方。
無観客開催で行われ、選手達も関係者も自由に行動出来ない中、日本らしさと、歓迎と感謝の気持ちを現せる唯一の場が、開会式であり閉会式だったはずなのに。
『日本らしさ』を大切に発信しないなら、わざわざこんなに大変なリスクを背負ってまで、東京で開催した意味がないと思います。
日本には海外に誇れる文化や伝統が沢山あるのに残念でなりません。

まぁ今回の企画者は間違いなく日本を愛する日本人ではないでしょう。

今回の惨劇が今の日本の問題を浮き彫りにしたのは間違いないと思います。
日本人は今、日本が静かに他国に侵略されている現実を知るべきです。

今回の件で違和感を感じた人がいるならば、日本で今何が起きているのか？
今世界で何が起きているのか？
TVが報道していることは真実なのか？
聞こえのいい事ばかり言うその人は、本当に日本のことを考えているのか？
そもそも日本人なのか？
疑問を持ち、自ら調べよく考えるべきです。

日本がこれからも日本であり続ける為に、一人ひとりが考え行動し日本を守りましょう。そう言いたくなる程、今回の件は危機感を持ちました。

けれども選手の皆さんの活躍には毎日沢山の勇気と感動をもらいました。
本当に開催できて良かったです。

text:
鳥肌がやべえ
まじでコロナが無くて、観客ありで、このクオリティの開会式やってたら伝説になってたぞ。
今リアタイでパリ五輪の予告みてるけど、正直この東京五輪予告のクオリティのが圧勝。パリの街並みはそりゃ綺麗よ。けど街並みはオリンピックが招致されるくらいだからどこもハイレベルなんだよな。

そこで、綺麗な街並み以外でどう人々を魅了させるかというところで、日本にはアニメゲームという選択肢があった。これは、日本にしかない選択肢だが、間違いなく世界中の人がワクワクすることのできる選択肢だ。ゲームアニメなんて世界共通のワクワク要素やん。まさに遊び心という表現がふさわしいと思う。これ以上の世界中の人が共感する遊び心を表現できるカルチャーは他に存在しない。

つまり何が言いたいかというと、この東京五輪予告映像はまじで最高。

そしてやり直したいという気持ちとはちょっと違うんだけど、このレベチ予告があっただけになんか悔しいってのが腹の底にある本音

text:
You can find out what happened if you read Bunshun (weekly magazine). 
Original plan for the opening ceremony of tokyo2020 made by Mikiko (who was in charge of this flag handover ceremony) was supposed to start with the red bike from Akira, Mario, Pikachu, perfume, etc.  it was super cool and the IOC loved it. But unfortunately, Dentsu (largest advertising agency)and some politicians stole and destroyed the show for the money.

She got removed without notification and her whole plan was canceled. Mikiko with 500 talented staff were even about to start the rehearsal for the ceremony, though. She was threatened by them not to make this a big deal. She got sudden deafness for the stress.  The collusion between corporations and politicians, and discrimination against women, sexists are serious problem in Japan.

By the way, this video was also directed by MIKIKO.  However, due to various problems, MIKIKO had to suddenly decline the general manager of the opening ceremony of the Olympic Games.  As a result, the opening ceremony was like this.  As a Japanese, I wanted to show the world a better opening ceremony.  Lastly.  This opening ceremony is not truly cool Japan. text: I recently learned about it on internet news and YouTube. It seems that an advertising agency called Dentsu in Japan has changed the opening ceremony plan of Mr. mikiko, which was originally held at the Olympic Games, and eliminated Mr. mikiko. Originally, songs from Pokemon and Nintendo were also planned to be played. In addition, famous entertainers and Perfume were scheduled to perform. The anime AKIRA was scheduled to run around in the central sphere on a motorcycle. The concept of the opening ceremony of the Olympic Games was to showcase Japan from the past to the future. I was planning to see the continuation of Japan's takeover performance that I saw at rio Olympic. I'm very sad! Few Japanese people know this story yet. It is very disappointing. What I want to say is that this opening ceremony is simple and has some good points, but it may have seemed a little lonely, but in reality it was planned to see a more exciting opening ceremony. However, the Olympics that have already begun cannot be stopped. We support players from all over the world. And I hope that the coronavirus will end soon. from JAPAN

text:
この5年前の閉会式のビデオから今日まで、それはそれはいろいろなトラブルがあった。
信じられないことに開会式の1年、1ヶ月、1週間前になっても信じられないようなニュースが続いた。
でも4時間ある開会式、このコロナ禍でもきっと何かしら驚かせてくれるような
クリエイティヴが少しでも見られるんじゃないかな、と心のどこかで淡い期待を持っていた。
少しでも信じた自分がバカだった。
また数十年後のオリンピックで、若いクリエイターたちが汚い大人たちに邪魔されず、
このビデオをも越えるような開会式を演出してくれることを願う。

text:
0:57
これって前の東京オリンピックポスターのオマージュだよね…？
(写真バージョンのほう)

もしかして北島が投げてる赤いボールも全部、1964tokyoのライジングサンの太陽？だとしたら凄い隠しアイテム！ 
そう思って見返したら、あちこちにライジングサン出てきてた！
世界ではあのポスターの認知度すごく高いから誰でも「あぁ！」と気がつく。
この動画でも赤へのこだわりがすごくあるし、AKIRAの世界観で赤いバイクが疾走する予定だったし。
本当の案での開会式では、1964リスペクトしたこの赤いライジングサンを2020に繋いで引き継いでいく式になってたのかな？

そっちのショーが見たかったんだよ！
誰か企画書手に入れて、デジタルで再現してくれる猛者はおらんかー！？
author: @cci4560

text:
電通がこんな下らない式にしたことは、電通に広告任せてるスポンサー企業も裏切ったということ。日本の企業がオリンピックでショーケースのように自分の技術を遠慮なく発揮できるとき。開会式は世界でみんながみてる。その時に、あの日本の技術はどうやったの？我が国でも使える？とこれを機に世界に大々的に売り込むチャンスだった。
それを個人の思惑であのちっぽけなショーをやって企業の思惑もぶっ潰した。

これはもう、広告なんて電通には出せないでしょ。企業の電通離れが加速する。

電通佐々木は背任行為で電通を潰す張本人になるかもしれない。

text:
日本に7年前に留学きてもう日本の会社で働いている韓国人です。

本当にどうでもいい話ですが
この予告は韓国でもすごい評価をされるぐらい日本の魅力を見せてくれました。
私が日本にきてこのような「作品」を生で見れて日本という国で留学していることが誇りだと思ってました。
しかしこの前の開会式をみてなんとも言えない脱力感まみれになりました。
誰かの利益のために全てが歪んでいくこの状況が個人的にすごく悔しいです。
私は日本という国が持っている魅力を経験して、知っています。決してこんなもんではないと、だからみんな残ってるオリンピック期間中は全力を尽くしてほしいです。

Croyez vous que L Écriture parle sans raison ? C est avec la jalousie que Dieu aime L Esprit qui habite en nous. Cependant, la grâce qu il accorde est plus grande encore c est pourquoi L Écriture dit : Dieu s oppose aux orgueilleux, mais il fait grâce aux humbles.

Jacques 4 v 5 à 6

Les gens pensent que le travail manuel est déshonorant et pourtant on joue à qui mieux à la gymnastique, au handball, au football ou encore à la 🥊 boxe. L ennemi est ravi des êtres humains employer leurs forces physiques et mentales à des activités DE COMPÉTITION qui ne les aident pas à être une bénédiction auprès de ceux qui ont besoin de leur aide.

Alors que les jeunes deviennent experts à des jeux pour eux mêmes et pour les autres, L ennemi de nos âmes, leur retirant les talents accordés par Dieu pour les remplacer par ses propres attributs.

En conclusion, Dieu ne prive pas L HOMME A JOUER A UN SPORT MAIS IL N APPRECIE PAS LA COMPÉTITION QUI MÈNE L HOMME AUX ILLUMINATIS

Seems like the girls chosen for Rio, and the ones who didn’t make the US team in Rio were stronger. I understand all the US girls had gone through the abuse of Nassau and the aftermath, but I am wondering how the athletes would do under Martha..if they would score higher in their individual standings in qualifying cations and team finals?

text: @@Jac-Jay Martha may have been over the line on a number of occasions with a lot of them, but she comes from a different system of sports building and education. Both her and Bela, did everything over the past 30 years or so to make champions. The Nassar situation that is just another sick thing, but solely speaking about Martha,Bela and their training techniques.. they work...and they shaped the U.S. gymnastics scene from the early 1980's. They changed U.S. gymnastics and paved ways for champions because if their tought training.

外國人跳水為什麼壓不死水花?因為他們個個都留長頭髮,就算跳得很好,在1O米臺跳下紮起的頭髮衝向水面一定造成很大的水花。雙手護頭讓水花消失,但是頭髮紮起讓水花高升,所以中共所有跳水隊員從小跳水到退休前跳水都是剪短頭髮的。
中共的跳水隊員的身體個個都很矮小,像小石頭掉落水里衝擊力不大,外國人身體又高又大件像一個大石掉在水里,請問水花大不大。

text:
Two different Polish lineups ran at 2019 World Athletics Championships and at the Tokyo Olympics. 
Doha: Wiktor Suwara, Rafał Omelko, Iga Baumgart-Witan, Justyna Święty-Ersetic
Tokyo: Karol Zalewski, Natalia Kaczmarek, Justyna Święty-Ersetic, Kajetan Duszyński
So Justyna Święty was the only runner who was a member of both teams. Interestingly in Tokyo she ran slower than in Doha (at the Olympics Święty was running with a not-fully-healed injury). It just shows how well the rest of the team performed.
author: @alialibaba1886

text: The Polish team was just experimenting with the order. There was another team in a different race than tried the same thing.....I think it was the team from Nigeria. They all came to the conclusion not to play psychological games and are just doing like everyone else.....male, female, female, male . You have to remember that the 4x400 mixed was just started recently.
author: @peterj5083

text: It is a myth that Poland won just because it changed the order of runners (MMFF->MFFM). As I wrote before in Tokyo Justyna Święty ran slower than in Doha, but the rest of the team performed much better.  For example Natalia Kaczmarek was more than 1 second faster than Iga Baumgart at the World Championships, Karol Zalewski was also more than 1 second faster than Wiktor Suwara,  It says something about this race.

Because they preferred to compete in individual events as well. They ran in some relays but they could not run in all relays, as well as individual events and expect to win them all.
People seem to forget that USA was on times supposed to win this event easily as they were more than 1.5 seconds ahead of the next best team on times run.
Unfortunately, Olympic events are won on the day based on what happens on the day not times on paper. Germany and Jamaica were virtually eliminated early due to baton changes etc  yet Jamaica would have been favourite for silver with an outside chance to beat USA. 
But as I said, races are won on the day not on projections. The Polish team ran the best race of all the competitors on the day and won the event. Well deserved victory

text:
The character models all look like they're taken from Crusader Kings but, for their shouts of victory sound-effects, with dying sounds taken from old 4-3 aspect ratio Kung Fu movies. 
The games generally speaking seems pretty good in the sense that there are enough worthwhile games in there even if the person only plays some of them.
The table-tennis looks cool, and volleyball, BMX, Basket-ball, and Rugby, as does the gamings about the soccerers and soccereresses. As for the other sports video-games genres _(swimming, running and the like),_ some of those work better if more about player stats, like a spreadsheet-game, like Championship-Manager rather than actually playing the sport. The hammer-throw could be redesigned like that. The boxers look kinda of cool, although that genre is a bit like wrestling (and martial-arts or fencing) whereby the Bushido-Blade or Fire-pro-wrestling on GBA with carefully planned moves can be a favourable way (sometimes) to design it. The Judo looks to be "sort of" doing that. The sport-climbing resembles a rhythm-time game akin to Frets-of-fire which is fine if the player is happy with that genre-swap. Again though, a manager-style game-genre could have been used. The baseball could also be done in a manager game genre however, competing with Mario Superstar Baseball (Gamecube) is hard to do and it has a reputation as a difficult game to master. The Tokyo2020 game, while designed to be appealing to the unwashed masses of the console-peasants app-style mobile gamer for the sales, looks like it nonetheless does make some effort to have some more thoughtful gameplay mechanisms.
_"OKayishly OK: 10/10"_ *(IGN)*
My comment has no hate in it and I do no harm. I am not appalled or afraid, boasting or envying or complaining... Just saying. Psalms23: Giving thanks and praise to the Lord and peace and love. Also, I'd say Matthew6.

text: Fillipo Tortu is one of only two  Caucasian men to run the 100m under 10 seconds. The other is the now retired Christof Lemetrie of France. Tortu's personal best is 9.99 seconds and Lemetrie's is 9.98. Tortu ran out of his skin to beat that athlete from Great Britain to the tape. It was an unbelievable effort from the Italian. Tortu also ran the anchor for Italy in the 4x100m final in Paris a few days ago, but this time he failed to hall in the anchor runner from Great Britain and, as a result, Italy finished outside the medals. Well done to Canada, South Africa and Great Britain for going 1,2 and 3 respectively. It may not have been as exciting a final as in Tokyo, but it was a great race nevertheless!

text: Tortu was already quite famous in Italy way before the Tokyo Olympics and we expected him to be in the 100m final and maybe have a shot at the medals, because he broke the 10s barrier and the national record at a very young age. No one in Italy knew who Marcell Jacobs was before this final or even after this final until we saw him winning. That probably helped him, because all the pressure was on Tortu. So it might be a surprise for the rest of the world but it's not a surprise for Italians that Tortu could run like that.
author: @milvao3400

text: Jacobs in Italia lo conoscono tutti ! Diciamo che sono due anni che finalmente è riuscito a esprimere il suo talento e le sue qualità.  Non dica cose che non sa !!!
author: @pvalbertof.5078

text: ​@@pvalbertof.5078 Forse è lei che non sa l'inglese... Prima delle olimpiadi Jacobs era sconosciuto ai più (al di fuori del mondo dell'atletica) mentre Tortu era già famoso da anni, per esser stato il primatista nazionale e per essere sceso sotto i 10 secondi da molto giovane, il che faceva ben sperare e tutte le attenzioni mediatiche erano su di lui, infatti faceva vari spot pubblicitari (fastweb ecc.), presenziava in tv e quant'altro... Jacobs no, era un atleta che aveva fatto salto in lungo fino a poco tempo prima.... e  prima di quelle Olimpiadi, prima della finale olimpica direi, tutti si aspettavano un qualche risultato da Tortu e non da Jacobs, anche quando si è qualificato per la finale non ci credeva nessuno, ma non per demerito, quanto perché non conoscevano Jacobs, semplicemente, e vedevano favoriti altri atleti... e questo può aver sicuramente influito perché ha liberato Jacobs da qualche pressione mediatica e aspettativa in più che Tortu invece ha dovuto attraversare. All'estero, invece, prima di questa staffetta, tutti sapevano chi era Jacobs, perché evava già vinto la gara individuale, mentre nessuno (parlo sempre di grande pubblico) sapeva chi fosse Tortu. Ecco perché si sono stupiti della vittoria nella staffetta... Stavo semplicemente spiegando questo, usi un traduttore la prossima volta invece che lasciare commenti insensati

text: I think women are possibly being less empathetic in response to the lack of empathy that we typically receive from men. My father is notorious for not listening with empathy and judging me or trying to offer solutions when I am simply seeking an empathetic ear. My mother will compare her experiences although is more empathetic and validating with her supportive listening skills. I will say that as women, we have traditionally been more empathetic to our own detriment. Hearing this conversation, I will definitely watch how I respond listening to my male friends as I do not want to come off as not being empathetic or sympathetic as that’s not my nature and who I want to be as a human being. I was talking to a close male friend last week and although I honestly believe I was empathetic, maybe I came off as somewhat apathetic because I definitely believe that he was complaining even though as a WM he’s literally at the top of the food chain. Maybe my unvocalized, Bruh Really, came through a bit. 🤦🏽‍♀️

text:
This isn’t some cheery nonsense about sportsmanship or recognizing greatness. Degrasse’s playing psychology and Bolt is calling him out on it.

This is a semi-final. Degrasse knew he could outspeed Bolt in the final the next day, but he did figure he could recover better than Bolt did. So he pegged it hard in the semi to push Bolt, hoping that it’ll tire Bolt out before the next day’s race.

Bolt’s not enjoying the moment. He’s telling Degrasse off that there was “no reason to run this fast.” Degrasse’s just being sheepish that he’s being caught.

text:
Here in 2024 as the games go on…. the Jamaican National Anthem is the ONLY ONE  IN THE WORLD THAT IS IN THE FORM OF A PRAYER….WRITTEN  by Reverend Hon. Hugh Sherlock, the music was composed by Hon. Robert Lightbourne, and the anthem was arranged by Mapletoft Poulle and Christine Alison Poulle…It was originally performed at the National Stadium in Kingston, on August 6, 1962, during the official Independence  ceremonies…..the Union Jack came down, n the BLACK, GREEN N GOLD ascended….mi was in Primary School at the timen mi heart string nearly buss….Y…in part because of this poem we had to learn to recite by heart , n its  words , that to moi, resonated in our choice of colours…. 

Nature by H.D. Carberry

We have neither summer nor winter
neither autumn nor spring.
We have instead the days
when the gold sun shines
on the lush canefields - magnificently.
The days when the rain beats
like bullets on the roofs
and there is no sound
but the swish of water in the gullies
and trees struggling in the high Jamaica winds.
Also there are the days
when leaves fade from off guango trees
and the reaped canefields
lie bare and fallow to the sun.
But best of all, there are the days
when the mango and the logwood blossom
When bushes are full of the sound of bees
and the scent of honey.
When the tall grass sways and shivers
to the slightest breath of air.
When the buttercups have paved the earth with yellow stars
and beauty comes suddenly, and the rains have gone.

text:
Fast, furious and a well deserved victory.

After the race: Fraser-Pryce looking furious, Jackson looking like her protege both walk up to Thompson-Hera, give her a customary congratulatory pat and walk away. No acknowledgement, no eye-contact, no exchange whatsoever - cold. Something's obviously going on there...

Aftermath: Thompson-Hera dominates for the 200m gold to get an unprecedented double double. Fraser-Pryce fades into fourth place. Jackson didn't even make the finals.

text:
What Tokyo showed at the closing ceremony of the Rio 2016 Olympics showed us that Tokyo 2020's opening ceremony would be something grand. There was even spoiler released in the media that was even scheduled an artificial meteor shower. Due to the coronavirus pandemic there was a change of directors responsible for organizing the party who changed their original plans so what we saw unfortunately was something very simple compared to other editions of the games. But I hoped that at least the Olympic cawdron (although very beautiful) would fly or be suspended from the ground, which didn't happen, for me it was the biggest disappointment. I thought that the Tokyo 2020 Olympic Games cawdron would surpass Rio 2016, that for me was disappointing.
In my opinion the international olympic committee should give the Japanese a second chance (of course if they wanted to) by granting the 2036 Olympic Games headquarters to be hosted again in Tokyo as the Japanese people deserve a second chance. So what we see now in 2021 would be the first part of the party and the second would be in 2036. From Brazil🇧🇷 ❤️🇯🇵

text: Pienso que las políticas no deben influenciar en los deportes, la ganadora de estos Juegos Olímpicos fue Dina. Si fuera por caídas, Yana en el 2016 tuvo una performance fallida en masas ,  quedó segunda y Margarita fue la ganadora.

text: No tiene que ver con políticas, sino con el código... cuando Margarita y Yana estaban en los JJOO, el código dictaba mucho más valor para la ejecución. 2017-2021 es diferente - con dificultad abierta (de aparato), los errores de ejecución son muy menos gravosos. Yana estaba 1) terminando su rotina; 2) durante un risco; 3) en un código cuya máxima dificultad es 10. La deducción de puntos es muy más significativa para ella que para Linoy, que estaba con dificultad total de 18-19.5... Simplesmente la dificultad de Linoy es más alta que la de todas las gimnastas, y eso le ha permitido fallar y ganar. No hay politica, solo un código que - para bien o mal - no previlegio la ejecución. Espero que tenga ayudado 😇 pero puedes leer la review de ClematisRG en fororitmica!

text: I believe Dina Averina was robbed. In Rio 2016 Yana Kudryavtseva dropped one club at the end of her performance and 2,2 points were deducted. She knew that failure would weigh on her. Yana lost gold to Mamun. This time Linoy Ashram dropped the ribbon we all saw that and no points were deducted for it. Russia will always be the rival to beat.
author: @oscarulisestorresornelas9914

text:
But Yana was performing a risk, so when she lost the club, she was not only penalised by the loss of apparatus, her risk was also invalid and therefore, she didn't got the point. Hence why she was heavily penalised. 
Margarita Mamum explained it well in a former interview. 
Here, Ashram lost the ribbon between 2 moves. Not during a risk (which would have been more penalised). 
Also, the Code of Point 2017-2021 was made to be more forgiving on losses as long as you can cram Apparatus Difficulties in the routine.
author: @raniriharisonrina4281

text: @@raniriharisonrina4281 thank you for clarifying my point of view. I didn't know that! The differences about loosing the apparatus during a risk or between two moves. It makes me think you practice rhythmic gymnastics because you know many things. I'm an admirer of this sport that is quite a spectacle. My trip has been a bit strange so far, I started with Simon Biles in the artistic and ended with the rhythmic gymnastics 🤪. I hope you can correct me any other time if you are willing. Greetings from México!!!

@@oscarulisestorresornelas9914 😅 I am not practicing the sport, but I follow it since I saw Evgenia Kanaeva on TV at the Beijing Olympics 2008.

text: They have a code of points and also the judges evaluate their choreographies in terms of technique and execution (plus, they have to do their choreography as they learnt it). If they lose balance, if they lose an apparatus, if they change part of the choreography (for example, changing a difficult move or trick for something less complicated, such as doing 2 turns instead of 4) they will get a deduction. There are a lot of judges and each one evaluates a different thing, from handling the apparatus to follow the beat of the music, from not losing balance to catch the apparatus properly. A lot of the gymnast got deductions that most people won't realize, but judges do, that's why even tho some girls did AMAZING they didn't achieve a great great score, because they planed perhaps something more difficult and ended up changing their routine for some easier elements. text:
This might be my favorite podium of the entire Olympics because of how great of a story it all is.

First we had a shared bronze medal which I think is really cool, you don't always have to seperate two medalists.
Then we had Vanessa Ferrari FINALY getting her Olympic medal after finishing fourth in the last two Olympics.
Lastly we had Jade Carey who in just 24 hours was able to bounce back from her failure in the Vault Final (which probably was the worst moment in her career) and win the gold medal.
author: @RickeGnool

text: The sportsmanship between these gymnasts is beautiful, and gives me hope for the rest of the world. You didn't see that at the Olympics before, especially between America and Russia. But the level of respect they have for their fellow athletes makes my heart happy

text:
Finals are determined by the top eight scores in qualficiations. Only two gymnasts per country can qualify for finals. Skinner finished in 4th place in vault qualifications behind Simone and Jade, so she was two per countried out of the final despite making the top ten. When Simone withdrew, she was able to compete as the second US vaulter. 

 Jade and Simone were the only US gymnasts to qualify for floor finals, so when Simone withdrew, the spot went to the gymnast who had the next highest scores in qualifications (not a gymnast from the US).

text: Individual vs team effort: Well before year 2000, drafting on the bike section was strictly prohibited. Thanks to this, triathlon was a really hard individual sport. Later ITU introduced drafting to make triathlon more presentable and enjoyable to the viewers. (Questionable decision, but that's OK.) With this decision triathlon partly became a team sport. Those who think this is BS, should try to perform 40K on bike with around 40km/h alone, or in the middle of a group. Drafting helps even mediocre bikers to stay in "business" with no hard effort. That's what I call "team effort" with huge advantage taken. Do happily holding hands in the last few meters qualifies as team sport with no hard effort? With no advantage taken at all? Really?

text: Anyone who wants to visit Japan must know that there is a possibility of being exposed to radiation.  The Japanese government claims that the Fukushima nuclear power plant situation that was caused as a result of the 2011 East Japan Earthquake was resolved, but this is false news.  Like the Chernobyl nuclear accident, radioactive pollution does not go away over hundreds of years.  In addition, they are trying to hold the Olympic Games in the area where the incident took place.  The Japanese government should immediately stop lying and disclose what is happening in the area.

text:
If you are planning a trip to Japan, I would recommend you to search for "Fukushima rice" on Youtube right away and decide.
Many Japanese foods made with rice contaminated with radioactivity produced in Fukushima will seriously harm your health and curse your descendants.
Currently, a large amount of rice is Currently, a large amount of rice is produced every year in Fukushima, Japan's radiation-exposed area, but it can never be sold to Japanese consumers. After purchasing a large amount of rice from the Japanese government, the rice from Fukushima was secretly supplied in large quantities through hotels, restaurants, and many catering establishments that are frequented by tourists, and is now being consumed by tourists. Perhaps it is very likely that the rice you bought at a tourist resort restaurant in Japan was contaminated with radioactivity produced in Fukushima.
The Japanese government has officially produced in Fukushima.
The Japanese government has officially announced that it will provide food to athletes from various countries participating in the Tokyo Olympic Games in 2020 by making agricultural products and various kinds of food products produced in Fukushima where the nuclear power plant exploded. The Japanese government is in the position to announce to the world that agricultural products, livestock products and seafood produced in Fukushima are safe from misunderstandings of contamination of radioactivity.

text:
Hello everyone. 
I live in Tochigi, next to Fukushima.
And it's population is around 2 million.
So far, every one of us have never felt the effects of radioactivity.
So we keep living here.
Also, 14 million people live in Tokyo because Tokyo is safe!
Many people (I think most of them is Korean) here seem to compain about radioactivity in Tokyo, but, what do you know about safety in Tokyo? Are you in Tokyo?
If Tokyo were really unsafe because of radioactivity, why are so many people living here and staying healthy?
If you are not in Tokyo and complain about radioactivity, you are ignorant.
I can't understand why so many people recommend other people not to go Tokyo even though many people are living thare healthily. 
And some people here said that Japanese media were lying, but, how did you know that? Is your information really correct? 
Tokyo was chosen to be host for Olympic Games because experts knew that Tokyo was safe!
Many foreigner have already visited Tokyo to see Rugby World Cup so you don't need to worry about it.

To Korean
Pyeongchang was so great!
Then, why do you want to bother next Olympic?
Tokyo is close to your country, so you can enjoy Tokyo Olympic easily as well as Pyeongchang.
I think it's great!
I konw how much you hate Abe, but Olympic is celebration of peace and politics doesn't matter.
If you think that Tokyo is really unsafe and afraid about it, it's okay.
But please stop bothering next Olympic just because you hate Japan.

we shouldn't be at the mercy of politics.

On this day he wrote history. 

Even as a mere spectator you could not take your eyes of the screen as he concentrated all of your attention on his.
He became part of the legend, carving his achievement directly into the fabric of sport history. Three times he charged and three times he rose up high and on his final attempt he flew. 
For a whole generation millions of people will remember Duplantis making this jump in Paris. Truly awe inspiring.

text:
Armand Duplantis was the first in history to conquer a height of 6.15 meters outdoors.

Swedish track and field athlete Arman Duplantis set a new world record in outdoor pole vaulting.

At the stage of the Diamond League in Rome, the 20-year-old athlete reached a height of 6.15 meters, surpassing by a centimeter the famous achievement of the Ukrainian Serhii Bubka, which no one could beat for 26 years.

text:
I’m going to yap now.

    Sympathy is different than empathy. These are a few ways that they are different things, as well as a few examples. 
    Sympathy is knowing what someone is going through. For example, if someone’s mother dies, you know that they are sad, but your mother didn’t die, did she? Therefore, you do not understand what they are going through. 
    Empathy is when you understand someone’s situation. Let’s go back to our example. Imagine that this year, your mother dies. Next year, your friend’s mom suffers the horrible yet relieving fate of death. You would understand them, because you’d been through the same thing.
    Sympathy is knowing, empathy is understanding. I pray that no one here will ever have to feel empathy who is a victim of abuse, sexual assault, alcohol addiction, or self hatred. But life is life, and you never know what may happen.
    These are two different things, and sometimes we must not reach to empathize, but only sympathize from afar. Appreciate the beauty of life, without ruining it, so that you won’t need to empathize. Make a change in the world, don’t follow these worldly things. It’ll ruin you.

    Good luck in life!



I’m sorry for yapping…I was needing a break from fictional stories, so I wrote this…

text: This happened to me with high jump. I play U13 (soon U15) high jump and already had the gold metal. I was getting tired, and I was only one or two more heights away from the record, but my coaches took me off and told my parents that I was getting too weak and tired and took me out. I told my coaches to let me jump up until I ran out of tries, but then I found out that they had put me in a race that I wasn’t even suppose to run ( I do track aswel) I kinda felt a little betrayed, despite almost having the record. Still kind of upset with them for this. But I’m definitely taking it next year.

text: "Try try until you succeed." This was a short quote introduced to me by me grade 2 english teacher.It's so short yet meaningful. It was by William Edward Hickson, a 19th-century English author and educational reformer. It is all about not giving up. It reminds us that life is full of challenges, and sometimes we might fail at something we really want to achieve. Instead of getting discouraged, it encourages us to keep putting in the effort, learning from our mistakes, and trying again. Success doesn’t always come easily or quickly, but with persistence and determination, we can reach our goals. It’s a heartfelt nudge to embrace the journey and keep going, no matter how tough things get.

text: And 20 days after this…he broke the 6.25m again…it currently stands at 6.26m!
author: @SeanShimamoto

text:
He’s actually American, he was born and raised in Lafayette, Louisiana and went to high school there. He was planning on competing for Team USA, but the Swedish coach (since he has both Swedish and USA citizenship) told him that his dad could be a coach on the Swedish team, so he decided to go that route.

Anyway, in pole vaulting, since 1994, no man could ever vault over 6.15m (20 ft 2 in)…the world record stood at 6.14m from 1994 to 2014. In 2014, a Frenchman recorded a height of 6.16m (20’2.5”)! That record would stand for another 6 years…until a 20-year old Armand Duplantis broke it with a height of 6.17m on 02/08/2020. His record wouldn’t stand for very long though….on 02/15/2020, one week later, it was broken with 6.18m…by Armand Duplantis. LOL. 

The key to know is that Armand gets a bonus every time he breaks a world record! So what does he do? He increases the height by 0.01m each time.

Two years later, on 03/08/2022, he hit 6.19m…two weeks later 6.20m…4 months later 6.21m…8 mos later, 02/25/2023 he hit 6.22m…7 mos later, 6.23m…

And in 2024:
On Hitler’s birthday, he crossed 6.24m…
At the Olympics, on 08/05/2024, he recorded 6.25m…
And 20 days later, 08/25/2024, he broke the world record for a record 10th time and it currently stands at 6.26m or 20 feet 6¼ inches!

That’s almost 4 inches more than his first world record…and nearly 5 inches over the 1994 record! 

Sergey Bubka, from Ukraine, held the world record from 08/31/1984 to 07/31/1994…he broke the WR 14 times and raised it from 5.91m to 6.14m (7¾”). This was from when he was 21 until he was 31 years old. 

Armand has broken the WR a total of 10 times so far, raised it from 6.16m to 6.26m (3¾”)…he first broke the WR when he was 20, and he’s still only 24 years old. He’s already won the 2020 Tokyo Olympic🥇and the 2024 Paris Olympic🥇…

Even crazier is that as of the 2016 Rio Olympics, the Olympic record was only 6.03m! At the 2020 Tokyo Olympics, Armand won🥇with a height of 6.02m! At the 2024 Paris Olympics, in the finals, Armand was the only man to clear 6.00m…meaning that he was guaranteed the🥇. On his next vault, he asked to have the bar raised to 6.10m, in order to comfortably set a new Olympic record…he has 3 tries to clear it…and he cleared it on his first attempt. He then had one more opportunity to vault, and he asked them to raise it to 6.25m…so that he could break his own world record of 6.24m. Armand would miss his first two attempts…but then he easily cleared the bar at 6.25m. He SHATTERED the Olympic record with a height of 6.25m!  That’s an increase of 9 inches!!! And set a new world record as well.

Fun fact: KC Lightfoot, from Team USA, holds the 4th highest vault, ever, at 6.07m. He finished 4th at 2020 Tokyo Olympics. Oddly enough, Armand was born on 11/10/1999…while KC was born on 11/11/1999.

text:
Me: S-senpai… I just… I really admire you. Not just your videos but… you. Like… (blushing) the real you.

Lebron James (blinking): Huh…?

[He pauses, his hand frozen over the “publish” button. The air between us changes. Time slows. Suddenly, the background fades into soft pink gradients. The world holds its breath.]

Me (inner monologue): DID I JUST SAY THAT OUT LOUD!? Abort mission—no wait, commit to the bit!

Lebron James (quietly): You’re serious…?

Me (nodding shyly): I… I think I’ve fallen for you. L-like… full anime confession under the sakura tree style…

[Wind blows. Cherry blossoms appear. A dramatic lens flare crosses his glasses—he’s not even wearing glasses.]

Lebron James (softly): Then I guess there’s something I’ve been holding back too…

[He steps closer. I can barely breathe. Our faces are just inches apart. His eyes soften. My heart is doing cartwheels into another dimension.]

Lebron James (gently): Can I…?

[He leans in. I freeze. My cheeks burn. I nod, just barely.]

Me (whisper): Y-yeah…

[And then—our lips meet. Soft. Warm. Tender.]

[A single cherry blossom petal floats between our lips and disappears into sparkly particles. Somewhere, a heart-shaped lens flare bursts.]

Lebron James (pulling back slightly): …That was better than a million likes.

Me (dazed, blushing hard): Senpai… y-you just crashed my heart’s server…

text: For those unfamiliar with figure skating yes these guys are incredible, but the finer details make it even more worthy. text:
There are several reasons why someone may not be as fast as the fastest man alive, and many of these reasons are related to genetics, training, and physical conditions. Here are a few:

1. **Genetics**: One of the biggest factors is genetic predisposition. The fastest man alive, such as Usain Bolt, possesses a unique combination of physical attributes that make him exceptional. He has an ideal limb length-to-body ratio, a high proportion of fast-twitch muscle fibers, and natural biomechanics that allow him to accelerate and maintain speed more efficiently than most people. While training can improve performance, some individuals may simply not have the same genetic advantages.

2. **Muscle Composition**: Fast-twitch muscle fibers are essential for explosive speed and power. The fastest runners typically have a higher percentage of these muscle fibers, which are more suited for sprinting. On the other hand, someone with a higher percentage of slow-twitch fibers would excel more in endurance activities but might not reach the same top speeds as someone with more fast-twitch fibers.

3. **Training and Technique**: Speed isn’t just about raw power; technique and specialized training are essential. World-class sprinters spend years perfecting their form, starting with their initial burst off the blocks to their stride mechanics and maintaining optimal posture while running. Without the proper coaching, training, and technique refinement, it’s much harder to reach top speeds, no matter how physically gifted a person may be.

4. **Nutrition and Recovery**: Proper nutrition, rest, and recovery are crucial for an athlete to perform at their best. Elite athletes like the fastest sprinters have access to expert nutritionists, personal trainers, and physiotherapists who ensure they stay in peak condition. Someone who isn’t following a specialized diet or recovery regimen may not be able to reach their full potential.

5. **Mental Factors**: Mental fortitude and focus are also important when competing at the highest levels of speed. The fastest people are often mentally strong, able to push through pain and fatigue in ways others cannot. A lack of mental resilience or confidence in one’s abilities can hinder an individual from reaching their fastest possible speeds.

6. **Injury History**: Past injuries can also play a significant role in an individual’s speed. Even a seemingly minor injury can affect a sprinter’s biomechanics, causing them to run less efficiently or with a reduced range of motion. Over time, these accumulated effects can significantly slow someone down, preventing them from reaching their potential.

In the end, while someone may not be the fastest man alive, they can still achieve impressive speeds with the right combination of genetics, training, and determination. However, only a rare few will have the ideal mix of attributes that allow them to rival the fastest athletes on the planet.
